snippet.textDisplay:
As a person who could and did paint shirts as a kid... It got old making entire pictures or scenes, before long...
But if you are just trying to make an old piece of clothing pop or give accent to something that is sort of plain, then yes, it can be fun.

Maybe I am a bit jaded, having had access to those supplies and making so many that I just got bored with it.
Jaded or not, people usually focus on the bright sides and silver linings, no matter which side of the fence they are on or which side of the window they are looking through (esp. when talking about "what if"s)
